        <div n="235-700B" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-235-700B-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-235-700B-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-700B-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-235-700B-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-235-700B-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-700B-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-235-700B-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-235-700B-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-700B-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-700B-line-1"> Beneath this verdant hillock lies&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-235-700B-line-2"> Demar, the wealthy &amp; the wise.<gap/><gap/></l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-235-700B-line-3"> His heirs that he may safely rest,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-235-700B-line-4"> Have put his carcase in a chest;</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-235-700B-line-5"> The very Chest, in which they say,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-235-700B-line-6"> Is other self, his Money, lay.</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-235-700B-line-7"> And, if his heirs continue kind</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-235-700B-line-8"> To that dear self he left behind,</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-235-700B-line-9"> I dare believe, that four in five</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-235-700B-line-10"> Will think his better half alive.235-700B   </l></lg></div>
